---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Uses — wekzs" description="The tools, apps, and gear I use day to day.">
  <section class="page-uses">
    <h1 class="gradient-title g-orange">Tools. Apps. Gear.</h1>

    <p class="uses-intro">
      People often ask which <strong>tools and gear</strong> I use for testing and day-to-day work.
      This isn't a static page — it's a <strong>living document</strong> with everything I'm using nowadays.
    </p>

    <div class="uses-group">
      <h2>Testing &amp; QA</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Playwright</strong> — my main automation framework, written in TypeScript.</li>
        <li><strong>Cypress</strong> — still reach for it on certain projects.</li>
        <li><strong>Postman</strong> — API testing, collections, and quick checks.</li>
        <li><strong>Burp Suite</strong> — REST API testing and security analysis.</li>
        <li><strong>k6</strong> — performance and load testing.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="uses-group">
      <h2>Dev &amp; CI</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>VS Code</strong> — my editor of choice, with the Dracula theme.</li>
        <li><strong>GitLab CI / GitHub Actions</strong> — pipelines for automated test runs.</li>
        <li><strong>iTerm2 + zsh</strong> — terminal setup I live in.</li>
        <li><strong>MySQL</strong> — database validation and data-integrity checks.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="uses-group">
      <h2>Tracking &amp; Docs</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Jira</strong> — issue tracking and sprint boards.</li>
        <li><strong>Confluence</strong> — test plans, documentation, and knowledge base.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="uses-group">
      <h2>Desk</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>MacBook Pro</strong> — daily driver. <em>(update with your exact model)</em></li>
        <li><strong>Monitor</strong> — <em>(add your monitor here)</em></li>
        <li><strong>Keyboard</strong> — <em>(add your keyboard here)</em></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
